anyone know how to make the mongolian beef dish from pf chang's it is simple and delicious and i would love to make it at home p f chang's mongolian beef min min prep servings change to servings us metric teaspoons vegetable oil teaspoon ginger minced tablespoon garlic chopped cup soy sauce cup water cup dark brown sugar cup vegetable oil lb flank steaks cup cornstarch large green onions make the sauce by heating tsp of vegetable oil in a medium saucepan over med low heat don't get the oil too hot add ginger and garlic to the pan and quickly add the soy sauce and water before the garlic scorches dissolve the brown sugar in the sauce then raise the heat to about medium and boil the sauce for minutes or until the sauce thickens remove it from the heat slice the flank steak against the grain into thick bite size slices tilt the blade of your knife at about a forty five degree angle to the top of the steak so that you get wider cuts dip the steak pieces into the cornstarch to apply a very thin dusting to both sides of each piece of beef let the beef sit for about minutes so that the cornstarch sticks as the beef sits heat up one cup of oil in a wok you may also use a skillet for this step as long as the beef will be mostly covered with oil heat the oil over medium heat until it's nice and hot but not smoking add the beef to the oil and saut for just two minutes or until the beef just begins to darken on the edges you don't need a thorough cooking here since the beef is going to go back on the heat later stir the meat around a little so that it cooks evenly after a couple minutes use a large slotted spoon to take the meat out and onto paper towels then pour the oil out of the wok or skillet put the pan back over the heat dump the meat back into it and simmer for one minute add the sauce cook for one minute while stirring then add all the green onions cook for one more minute then remove the beef and onions with tongs or a slotted spoon to a serving plate leave the excess sauce behind in the pan Cuisine of Brazil Bengali cuisine Cuisine of Malaysia Hot dog D__ner kebab Donburi Steak Soul food Brewery German cuisine Hot pot Beef noodle soup Cuisine of Laos Ramen Jewish cuisine Haggis Breakfast Soup Peruvian cuisine Knife Wok Sushi Halva Bacon Pizza Coffee Nabemono Dim sum MRE Cuisine of Greece Cooking Satay Soy sauce Kebab Risotto French cuisine Roast beef Fish and chips Russian cuisine Chicken soup Jiaozi Cincinnati chili Cuisine of the Southern United States Idli Tea Domesticated turkey Bread Stock (food) Drill bit Dumpling In-N-Out Burger Sandwich Mayonnaise Soba Pasta Pancake McDonald's Corned beef Roux Dosa Rice pudding Cha chaan teng Cooking weights and measures Cuisine of Vietnam Cuisine of Thailand Shanghai cuisine Udon Kung pao chicken Food preservation Sugar beet Kelantan Horse meat Goulash Canadian Chinese cuisine Asado Italian beef Taiwanese cuisine Chopsticks 